## Syntax Setup

Maps also use curly braces `{}`, but they pair items using colons `:`.

```dart
Map<String, int> playerScores = {
  'Player1': 5000,
  'Player2': 2500,
  'Player3': 9999 
};
```
The Type is `<String, int>` because the Keys are Strings, and the Values are ints!

slides.codeSnippet:
void main() {
  Map<String, String> translation = {
    'hello': 'hola',
    'goodbye': 'adios'
  };

  // Adding a new word is easy!
  translation['water'] = 'agua';

  print( translation['hello'] );
}
